<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jimette</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, here are some shots of 3 resin gold helmets, about the closest we can get to the Armour of the Virtues colour.<P><IMG SRC=http://www.evilbastard.org/eq/goldhelmet.jpg><P>Step 1 : Make the dye Extract <BR>-----------------------------<P>Jack-O-Lantern fungus comes from three locations, but I can only confirm one.<P>-The Fairy Ring in Lesser Fay has some spawn on the ground that look like coin-sized mushrooms. These are very rare, and appear to be on a 22 to 24 hour real-life spawn.<P>-Jack-o-lanterns in Unrest, this may be bugged because they currently drop red dye. A Level 55 monk removes the population of unrest at a great rate of knots, and no fungus dropped.<P>-Jack-o-lanterns in West Karana - haven't had a chance to check yet, everytime I'm in West Karana I'm a bit tied up to check.<P>Once you have found a mushroom or two, go to the Windmills in Steamfont, the Armour Vendor in Highhold Pass or the Troll Vendor in Rathe mountains, and buy some of the 'Empty Vials' that are stackable.<P>Also, while you are there buy 3 x 'Resin' (5 plat each) and 1 flask of Acid and 1 flask of Resin. You'll need this in a little bit<P>Buy some ordinary store-bought water, and go looking for a Rogue or Shaman that owes you a favour. They should ideally have a poison making or alchemy skill of 40 or greater. Get them to combine the vial, the fungus and one flask of water (NOT summoned or foraged) in the poison kit / medicine bag. You should then get a 'Jack-o-lantern' extract.<P>Step 2 : Make the Dye itself<BR>----------------------------<P>Now you need to practice pottery. This is a very easy skill to advance, and you basically get a skill point every attempt. You need :<BR>- Medium Jar Sketch<BR>- Clay Block<BR>- Flask of Water.<P>This will make an Unfired Clay Jar. Make a few of these, they cost about 1 gold to attempt each one.<P>Buy some Quality Firing sheets, and take your clay masterpieces to a Kiln. Combine the jar and a firing sheet, and you get a four slot container with a combine button. As this is a container, you will need an inventory slot free, otherwise you will need to do some juggling.<P>Put the Jack-O-Lantern extract, and 3 resins into the clay container. Make sure the resins are *NOT* stacked, instead you should have the four slots each containing 1 item. <P>Hit combine. You should end up with single tube of 'Light Yellow Dye'.<P>Step 3 : Dying the armour<BR>-------------------------<P>Obtain a undyed Fine Steel Helmet from your local blacksmith, or make it yourself. I recommend not attempting to make Fine Steel armour unless your blacksmithing skill is over 150. You should pay between 60 plat (cost) and 200 plat for your helmet. <P>Walk up to a forge, put your helmet, 1 vial of Acid, 1 vial of Laquer and the dye in. Hit combine. <P>It seems that there is no skill roll for this, but occasionally (possibly 5%) there is a failure. In this event, you get the helm back, but lose the dye, so that's why you may wish to have a backup dye made during the long walk to this step.<P>I did this with a set of three dyes earlier today, and I succeeded dying all three. If you are on Bertox and take a medium, send me a tell and try to catch me in the same zone, I'll donate the other two helms to clerics who can track me down.<P>Colour chart :<P><IMG SRC=http://www.evilbastard.org/eq/final.jpg><P>Jimette<BR>56th Human Cleric, who had a copy of my post sitting in buffer<BR>Bertox</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Perplex Cerebrum</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Good gosh, why does the human helmet look as if your head got stuck while cleaning the inside of a furnace. *shakes head*<P><BR>very nice guide BTW.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">chrisstauf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fantastic guide...Way to give back to the cleric community. I think I will commision a guild smithy to make me one of those.<P>by the way...what skill did/do you have when you made this??<P>------------------<BR>Chrisstauf HealingSoul<BR>Priest of Light of the Karana Lightbringers<BR>40 times blessed by Mithaniel Marr<p>[This message has been edited by chrisstauf (edited 10-25-2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nemean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just as an FYI - the jack o lanterns (scarecrows) in West Karana drop sarcophagi fungi as well (ie the red ones).<P>So it looks like the ONLY place to get jack o lantern fungus is the fairy ring in faydark.  Grr.  Another long camp to pick something up off the ground.<P>Thanks Verant  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>Nem.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Seela Truelight</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am curious, I thought "Essence of Sunlight" was the gold dye, and that Jack-O-Lantern Fungus was more yellow. I got one tube of Essence of Sunlight a while back, apparently it is very rare. Anyone know the scoop on this?<P>------------------<BR>Seela Truelight<BR>L60 High Elf Cleric<BR>Rodcet Nife Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jimette</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Essence of Sunlight is a Temper component, not a dye. I know because I tried to get someone to extract it, and it wouldn't combine.<P>Jimette<BR>57th Human Cleric, and farmer of Sand Giants and Seafurys Extrodinaire.<BR>Bertox</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nige Willowleaf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">wow the HIE version looks SUPER! Way to go  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR><B><I>Nige Willowleaf</B></I><BR>58 Cleric <BR>Cazic Thule Server<BR>Officer, Sphere of Transcendence</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Troas Merwind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I can confirm an additional location for Jack-o-Lantern fungus.  Samhains in fear drop it as well.  But somehow I just can't see people farming fear for dye components...<P>------------------<BR>Troas Merwind<BR>Vicar of Tunare<BR>Saryrn</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Soulweaver</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I always found the SSB went quite nicely with my Armour of Virtue</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">blacadder</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Great post, this is a bit off topic but does anyone know how a Halfling can imbue or enchant a small fine plate helmet? Any recipies? I would like to add some stats to my helmet to go with the rest of my gold suit now that I know how to dye it.<P>Thanks!</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
